Stationary energy emissions are primarily due to fuel consumption for energy use in residential, commercial, and institutional buildings and facilities (commercial and public buildings such as schools, hospitals, government offices, temples, highway street lighting, and other public facilities) in the city. Specifically, emissions from fuel combustion (Scope 1) and grid-supplied energy consumed (Scope 2) within the city boundary were included. To explore the electricity dataset, real consumption data were obtained from the Provincial Electricity Authority (PEA). A scaled-down method using population indicator10 was employed to represent city-wide energy consumption. Equation 1 can be used to estimate CO2 emissions from energy use in this sector.1Energy GHG emissions=∑Energyusedi,j×EFij\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
